<TEXT>
An Australian who was sentenced to 
death on heroin trafficking charges was freed after the Supreme 
Court threw out the charges Corrections Department officials said 
Saturday 
The officials who spoke on condition of anonymity said Donald 
Tait 54 was released Friday and was awaiting deportation 
Tait of Sydney was arrested in July 1985 on the southern 
resort island of Phuket with 44 pounds of heroin in his suitcase 
according to police 
He pleaded innocent to charges of possessing heroin with intent 
to sell 
A provincial court sentenced him to death in November 1985 In 
January 1986 an appeals court in Bangkok overturned the verdict on 
grounds of lack of evidence and the Supreme Court upheld the 
appeal 
</TEXT>
